{<b>Responding to 1NT Summary</b>

When partner opens 1NT, you want to be sure to get the partnership to game (at
least) when you hold 10 or more points. Use the Stayman convention whenever you
have a hand with at least one four-card major suit. If you find a fit, bid game
in the major suit. If you don’t, bid game in 3NT.

Responder also can use the Stayman convention with a hand of invitational
strength (eight to nine points) and interest in finding a major suit. If a fit
is found, responder raises to the three-level to invite game. If no fit is
found, responder bids 2NT to show a hand of invitational strength.

<u>If not playing Jacoby Transfers</u>, responder also uses the Stayman convention to
show an invitational-strength hand with a five-card or longer major suit.
Responder starts with 2\C and then bids the major suit at the cheapest
available level if no fit has been found. Opener can pass or accept the
invitation by bidding game in notrump or the major suit.

Do not use Stayman with a weak hand (less than eight points) unless you are
short in clubs and are prepared to pass anything that opener rebids (<i>Garbage</i>
<i>Stayman</i>).}
[BCFlags "17"]

